\title{Cybernetic optics for sheaf assembly}
\taxon{definition}
\import{macros}

\p{Stage 2 (local processing / sheaf assembly) is a \strong{categorical
cybernetic system} ([[capucci-cybernetics-2021]]). Each local processor
is a bidirectional agent: forward pass computes spectral features,
backward pass receives Fisher-Rao gradient from the global loss.}

\p{The bidirectional structure is a dependent optic
([[capucci-dependent-optics-2022]]): the backward type depends on the
forward output. In BCI terms: the gradient signal depends on which
spectral features were extracted, because Fisher-Rao distance is
defined on the statistical manifold of the extracted distribution.}

\p{GF(3) encoding (HbO=+1, HbR=-1, baseline=0) quantizes the optic's
residual. The trit is the \em{coplay output} — the local processor's
contribution to the global conservation law.}
